						               													<description>Six letter dice (d6) are permanently mounted to a hexagonal device. Each player receives a pencil, a sheet from the notepad. The players pick one of the three interchangeable category dice (d12) and put it in the device. Then the start player rolls the device and places it on the middle of the table. Now, all players have to write down words matching the category of the category device. The initial letter of the words is determined by the letter dice. The start player of the round may call &amp;ldquo;stop&amp;rdquo; at any time, even if he has not yet found a suitable term for each letter. Any valid term that no other player has written down is worth one victory point. The game is played for four rounds. The player with the highest total score wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
